# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
Here we can observe some edge cases like when money is 4 and children is 1 and when money is less then children.We can approch this problem in constructive + greedy way to get ans maximum

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
1. Initialise a array pre of size children with value as 0.
2. If(money==4 and children==1) then it is impossible to distrubte the money among all children so here i return -1.
3. Distribute one money unit to each children and check if money is less than 0 or not, if it is less than 0 the it is impossible to distribute money among children hence i return -1 here.
4. Initialise the ans as 0 and traverse through the array. If current money is greater then 7 then increment the ans by 1 and decrease the moeney by 7 and add that 7 into pre[i].
5. else if money is less than 7 but greater than 0 then add all money into that pre[i] and money value will be 0.
6. At index n-1 we will check few condition to determine the ans.If pre[n-1] is 8 and money is stil left then return ans-1 else if there is no money left then return 0. If(pre[i]<8) the check if(pre[i]==4) if it is 4 then return ans-1.
7. Return ans at the end.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:O(N)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity:O(N)
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int distMoney(int money, int children) {
       vector<int> pre(children,0);
        if(money==4 && children==1) return -1;
        for(int i=0;i<children;i++)
        {
            pre[i]++;
            money--;
        }
        if(money<0) return -1;
        int ans=0;
        int n=children;
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++)
        {
            if(money>=7)
            {
                pre[i]+=7;
                money-=7;
                ans++;
            }
            else if(money>0)
            {
                pre[i]+=money;
                money=0;
            }
            if(i==n-1)
            {
               if(pre[i]==8)
               {
                   if(money>0)
                   {
                       return ans-1;
                   }
                   if(money==0) return ans;
               }
                else if(pre[i]<8)
                {
                    if(pre[i]==4)
                    {
                        if(i>=1)
                        {
                            return ans-1;
                        }
                    }
                }
            }
        }
      return ans;
    }
};
```

