solutions.content:
Rules that we have to follow
* All money must be distributed.
* Everyone must receive at least 1 dollar.
* Nobody receives 4 dollars.

<br>
When money can't be distributed to all the childrens.

```
if(children > money) return -1;
```

If every child can get at least 8\$, in that case all the children will get 8\$ except the last one because the last guy will get more than 8 dollers

```
if(8*children < money){
  return children-1;
}
```
If every child getting 8 dollers

```
if(8*children == money) return children;
```
**as we have came here means the money is smaller than 8\*children i.e 7*Children + children [ this money will be distributed to all the children initially to make sure everyone has atleast 1 dollers]<br>**

```
money = money-children;
```
**Here money will definately be smaller than 7*children**<br>
now
if ***money > 7*(children-1)** , we have to decide how many dollers last child is getting,if he is getting 4$  the answer will be children - 2,because that money will be distributed to 2 other children else we will return children-1
else return money/7
```
if(7*(children-1) < money){
	int r = money%7;
	if(r == 3)
		return children-2;
	return children-1;
}
```

**COMPLETE CODE**
<br>

```
class Solution {
public:
    int distMoney(int money, int children) {
        if(children > money) return -1;
        if(8*children < money){
            return children-1;
        }
        if(8*children == money) return children;
        money = money-children;
        if(7*(children-1) < money){
            int r = money%7;
            if(r == 3)
                return children-2;
            return children-1;
        }
        return money/7;
    }
};
```

