# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->

# Approach
It checks if the available money (money) is less than the number of children (child). If so, it returns -1 indicating that the distribution is not possible.

It calculates the initial division of money among the children by dividing money by child. The result is stored in the variable division.

It calculates the remaining amount of money (remain) after distributing the initial division equally among the children, excluding one child.

It creates a vector nums of size child and initializes all elements to -1. This vector will store the amount of money each child receives.

The first element (nums[0]) is set to the remaining amount (remain), while the rest of the elements are set to the initial division (division).

If the amount of money received by the first child (nums[0]) is less than or equal to 8, it enters a loop to redistribute the excess money.

a. It iterates through the children from index 1 to child-1.

b. If the amount of money received by a child (nums[i]) is greater than 1, it reduces that amount by 1 and adds it to the variable rem.

c. It then checks if the remaining amount (rem) is sufficient to increase the money of the child (nums[i]) to 8. If so, it adds the necessary amount to reach 8 and reduces rem accordingly.

d. After this loop, if there is still some remaining money (rem), it adds it to the last child (nums[child-1]).

If the amount of money received by the first child (nums[0]) is greater than 8, it enters a loop to handle the excess money.

a. It iterates through the children from index 0 to child-1.

b. If the amount of money received by a child (nums[i]) is greater than 8, it reduces it to 8 and adds the excess amount to the variable great.

c. If the amount of money received by a child (nums[i]) is less than 8, it checks if there is still some excess money (great) available. If so, it increases the money of the child by 1 and reduces great by 1.

d. After this loop, if there is still some remaining excess money (great), it adds it to the last child (nums[child-1]). Otherwise, if there is still some remaining money to be added (adder), it adds it to the last child.

It then iterates through the nums vector from index 1 to child-1 and checks if any child received exactly 4 units of money. If so, it reduces the money of that child by 1 and adds it to the previous child.

Finally, it counts the number of children (ans) who received exactly 8 units of money by iterating through the nums vector and increments ans whenever the value is 8.

If the count ans is negative, it returns 0. Otherwise, it returns the count ans.
# Complexity
- Time complexity:O(child)

- Space complexity:O(child)
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int distMoney(int money, int child) {
        if(money<child)     return -1;
        int division=money/child;
        int remain=money-division*(child-1);
        vector<int>nums(child,-1);
        nums[0]=remain;
        for(int i=1 ; i < child ; i++){
            nums[i]=division;
        }
        int rem=0;
        if(nums[0]<=8){
            for(int i=1 ; i < child ; i++){
                if(nums[i]>1){
                    rem=rem+(nums[i]-1);
                    nums[i]=1;
                }    
            }
            for(int i=0 ; i < child-1 ; i++){
                int a=8-nums[i];
                if(rem>=a){
                    rem=rem-a;
                    nums[i]=8;
                }
            }
            if(rem>0)   nums[child-1]=nums[child-1]+rem;
            else        nums[child-1]=nums[child-1];
        }
        int great=0;
        int adder=0;
        if(nums[0]>8){
            for(int i=0 ; i < child ; i++){
                int a=nums[i]-8;
                if(nums[i]>8){
                    great=great+a;
                    nums[i]=8;
                }
                if(nums[i]<8){
                    while(nums[i]!=8 and great!=0){
                        nums[i]++;
                        great--;
                    }
                }
                if(great==0 and nums[i]>1){
                    adder=adder+nums[i]-1;
                    nums[i]=1;
                }
            }
            for(int i=0 ; i < child-1 ; i++){
                int a=8-nums[i];
                if(adder>=a and nums[i]<8){
                    nums[i]=8;
                    adder=adder-a;
                }
            }
            if(great==0) nums[child-1]=nums[child-1]+adder;
            else        nums[child-1]=nums[child-1]+great;
        }
        for(int i=1 ; i<nums.size() ; i++){
            if(nums[i]==4){
                nums[i]--;
                nums[i-1]++;
            }      
        }
        int ans=0;
        for(int i=0 ; i<nums.size() ; i++){
            if(nums[i]==8) ans++;
        }
        if(ans<0)    return 0;
        return ans;
    }
};
```

