# Intuition
if we have more money then extra money give to the last child or less money then also give to the last child
(but first give all the childrens 1 dollar for pass the second condition of problem)

# Approach
Give every children 1 dollar for pass the second condition

Now, We have only ***3 condition*** to solve this problem
### [1] money distributes as per needed for first ```
children-1``` children but last children have 4 children which is not valid as per problem 3rd condition.
So, we have to leave last 2 children from giving 8 dollar.

### [2] For all children money distrubute completely 8 dollar per children(not more than 8 and not less)

### [3] money more than needed for all children or less than needed
   ***(i)*** If more than needed then give extra money(more then 8) to the last children but satisfies first ```
children -1 ```.
 ***(ii)*** otherwise money/7 (In JS this will give fraction number so we have to wrap with ```
Math.floor()```)

# Complexity
- Time & space complexity : O(1) - constant


```javascript []
var distMoney = function(money, children) {
    if(money < children){
        return -1;
    }

    money -= children;

    const helper = Math.floor(money/7);

    // 4 remaninig condition
    if(helper == children-1 && money % 7 == 3){
        return children-2;
    }
    // have as per needed
    if(money / 7 == children){
        return children;
    }

    // money more than needed then children-1 otherwise Math.floor(money/7)
    return Math.min(children-1,helper);
};
```
