## Intuition
After hitting 5 WA's I decided to go all out 🤧

## Approach
Made an array of size = children, each index will store the money given to the ith children. At the end, count how many children end up with exactly 8 money.
- Give 8 until you can do so.
- If you are to give 4, give 3 instead.
- If no money left, give one and take one from leftmost non-one element.

## Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int distMoney(int money, int children) {
        if(children > money) return -1;
        if(money == 4 && children == 1) return -1;
        vector<int> v (children);
        for(int i=0;i<children;i++){
            if(money >= 8){
                v[i] = 8;
                money -= 8;
            }
            else{
                if(money == 4){
                    v[i] = 3;
                    money -= 3;
                }
                else if(money == 0){
                    v[i] = 1;
                    int p = i-1;
                    while(p>=0 && v[p] == 1) p--;
                    if(p == -1) return 0;
                    v[p]--;
                }
                else{
                    v[i] = money;
                    money = 0;
                }
            }
        }
        int cnt = 0;
        for(auto i : v)
            cnt += (i == 8);
        if(money) cnt--;
        return cnt;
    }
};
```
Side Note : You could have given chocolates to the children :)

