# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
The number of the children is small, we can enumerate the number of children that can receive exactly 8 dollars and check if is valid.
# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Iterate from i = children to 0, we distribute exact 8 dollars to these children
Now we have 
the amount of money that have not been delivered yet (money = money - i * 8)
The amount of children who haven't received any money (children = children - i)
If money >= children and none of the following condition is satisfied, this is a valid distribution:
1. children == 0 && money > 0
2. money == 4 && children == 1 (this is the only case where the child must receive 4 dollars)
