# Intuition/Approach
1. First we distribute 1 to every child to satisfy 1 condition.
2. Then we see how many children can get 8.
3. Then we check if one only child is remaing after previous step and if that only has 1 so far then we need to change exsting distribution from step 2 to satisfy 3rd condition
4. If any money is remaining after this then we need to give it all to one child.


# Complexity
- Time complexity:
O(1) => since our input size does not effect our processing steps.

- Space complexity:
O(1) => since our input size does not effect our processing steps.

# Code
```
class Solution {
    public int distMoney(int money, int children) {
        // check condition 1 if that is successfull proceed else retuen -1
        int moneyRemain = money - children;
        if(moneyRemain<0){
            return -1;
        }
        // if money remaining after satisfying 1 is < 7 then no one can have 8 but all other 3 conditions are satisfied
        if(moneyRemain<7){
            return 0;
        }

