# Intuition
The worst task on the first view and solution is not so obviously. But...

# Approach
We need to give `1` to each child and calculate `drawback` for filling all of children:
* if `drawback` is `0`, then all children have 8 coins.
* if `drawback` is `4`, then we need distribute `1` extra point to some child so we have `2` children without 8 coins.
* if `drawback` is negative, then only one child will have extra coins.
* in other cases we need to calculate subtract children and division `drawback` by 7.

# Complexity
- Time complexity: we have no loops in this solution but if we calculate branches then complexity is `O(4)`.

- Space complexity: small :)

# Code
## TypeScript
![image.png](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/c35d299e-d1cb-4972-98a9-f5f670c6d28c_1683877671.0925624.png)
```typescript
function distMoney(money: number, children: number): number {
    if (money < children)
        return -1;

    const drawback = children * 8 - money;

    if (!drawback)
        return children;

    if (drawback === 4)
        return children - 2;

    if (drawback < 0)
        return children - 1;

    return children - Math.ceil(drawback / 7);
}
```
