```rust
impl Solution {
    pub fn dist_money(money: i32, children: i32) -> i32 {
        if money < children {
            return -1;
        }

        let drawback = (children * 8 - money) as f32;

        if drawback == 0_f32 {
            return children;
        }

        if drawback == 4_f32 {
            return children - 2;
        }

        if drawback < 0_f32 {
            return children - 1;
        }

        return children - (drawback / 7_f32).ceil() as i32;
    }
}
```
# Bitwise optimization
We can use bitwise operator instead of `Math.ceil`. Like this:
```typescript
