solutions.content:
**Idea:**
* Give $1 to each child
* If remainder < 0, then return -1, because this indicates a distribution is impossible
* Now we need to give $7 more to max children (eights)
* If `eights` = `children` and no money left, then all the children will get $8, return `children`
* Else if `eights` = `children - 1` number of children can be given $8 but remainder = $3, it means 1 of the children getting $8 will have to give $2 to the other one, so there will be `children - 2` number of children with $8, 1 with $6 and 1 with $5, so return `children - 2`
* Else at most `children - 1` number of children can get $8, but that would depend on how many `eights` we have remaining, so the min of these 2 will be the limiting factor, so return `min(eights, children - 1)`. This is the only tricky part here.
>**T/S:** O(1)/O(1)
```
public int distMoney(int money, int children) {
	money -= children;
	if (money < 0)
		return -1;

	var eights = money / 7;
	var remainder = money % 7;

	if (eights == children && remainder == 0)
		return children;
	if (eights == children - 1 && remainder == 3)
		return children - 2;
	return Math.min(eights, children - 1);
}
```
