maths and greedy
case 1: insufficient money: return 0
case 2: if money available is more even if all children get 8 money
case 3: if 8 is distributed and 1 child remains who with 4 money remaining
case 4: if all children have 8's but some money is left
case 5: if after distribution the leftover money is satifsying remaining children
case 6: we have insufficient left over money so we have to take from children having 8


Note: maybe the number of cases can be reduced, please comment for improvements. 
